parameters:
Ho ho ho. You've arrived, I've been waiting for you. To
think you easily repelled the demon army, quite impressive
indeed.
So you were here, Ho-Chiku! It's time to pay your dues!

We'll settle our battle from the red-light district right
here and now!

Momiji. It's been a while. To betray the Fuma and even side
with the enemy, Karin, our lord was quite furious, you know?
What...? Fuma... you say? Is that true, Karin?

Yes. Both Momiji-san and I are like the extremities of Fuma.
The red-horned war demons we've been fighting are survivors
from the village of Fuma--

Nyoho ho! To think you're the daughter of Lord Nakataro,
Karin. If you had become demons, you could have been our
allies.

Ho-Chiku or whatever your name is. I'm searching for a one-
eyed demon. Is it not among your comrades?

A one-eyed demon, you say? We do have one among our war
demons. Since Momiji here went missing, Lord Gyouon has been
brought in as one of the new Hachi-On War Demons. He's not
from Fuma, but a gigantic, grotesque war demon.

--! That creature is the hated enemy who laid waste to my
village! Where is it? Answer me!

Ho ho ho! There's neither obligation nor need to tell you.
After all, you all will perish miserably right here!

These guys are specially made, much more robust than
ordinary armored puppets. There are three of us and three of
you--a perfect match, wouldn't you say?

Of course. You too have overcome that tragedy as a fellow
survivor. We have become war demons and continue to fight--
it is our destiny.
...Understood. We will defeat you and move forward.

Ho ho ho ho! To think the timid girl who was swayed by her
surroundings has now gained such a fierce look in her eyes,
Momiji! But don't underestimate me? Feel the power of my
steel threads with your own body!
Here they come--! Yugiri-chan, Momiji-san! Are you ready?

Yes. Bring it on, old war demon! We will defeat you and then
crush the rest of the war demons!
--! I will go at full strength!

Don't underestimate us, little girls. We are survivors of
Fuma who have lived on as demons for over a hundred years.
We cannot afford to lose to humans! I'll slice you to
pieces!
--Ho-Chiku and the elite armored soldiers are attacking!

Gah...! Cough...!! To think... this is enough to defeat me
is laughable!
Huh! You still want to fight!?
Ho-Chiku-san, please stop! The fight is already...!

Surrender is out of the question. If you wish to stop me,
pierce my heart, Momiji.

If Momiji-dono cannot do it, then I shall deliver the final
blow.

(...To think an old man like me would live so long only to
meet such an end... Ho ho...)
You! The leader of the demons!?

Indeed. I have yet to tell you my name. I am known as Fuuma
Kotarou--now living as the demon Kotaro.

Heh. It's been 100 years since the age of civil wars--I'm
somewhat pleased that my name still lingers. However, it is
the law of the shinobi to kill those to whom they reveal
their name.

~~! (My heart won't stop pounding! If I fight now, I'll
die!)
Phew...hah...so you've come to see for yourself, my lord...

...Even with your skills, to suffer defeat at the hands of a
human. Can you still fight, Ho-Chiku?

Ho-ho... My apologies, Lord Kotaro. As you can see, Ho-Chiku
has been defeated... The guest was stronger than imagined,
an opponent beyond my grasp...

If it's only such injuries, then regeneration is possible.
Why do you not do so, Ho-Chiku?

...This humble one has grown weary of living. I thought it
reasonable to leave things to the younger generation and
fade away like dew at this juncture.

Serving the young Lord Kotaro and following him throughout
my life... It has been rather harsh for an old man. To not
die when it's time is nothing but miserable. Please show
mercy.

Is that so. You have worked hard until now. I thank you,
Hou-Chiku elder--

May glory be with the future of Fuuma... My lord...
Fare...well...
--Ho-Chiku collapsed to the ground as if crumbling...

Are you saddened by Ho-Chiku's death, Momiji? You were
treated like a real granddaughter in the village of Fuuma.
Yes... I am sad that Mr. Hou-Chiku has passed away. But...

But... more than that, seeing you continue to commit evil in
this world as a demon fills me with more anger than sorrow.

To curse your father whom you haven't seen in a long while?
What an unfilial daughter you are, Momiji--
--! Eh, daughter!? The leader of the demons is...!

Yes. Fuuma Kotarou is my father. And we parted ways over 30
years ago... Now he is my enemy.

I am Nakatarou's daughter, Karin. You have grown up from the
little baby you were. It seems you are searching for your
father... Do you wish to know his whereabouts?

--! If you know something, then tell me honestly! I've been
searching for my dad who disappeared five years ago!

Then let me speak frankly. Your father, Nakatarou--died five
years ago.

That's right. We happened to meet again in Edo five years
ago. He refused our invitation and thus met his death. A
fittingly pitiful end for a traitor who became a renegade
ninja.
~~~~! My dad... died!? That's a lie!!
...! Karin-chan! Wait! It's dangerous to attack recklessly!

I don't believe it! I'll take your head right here, the head
of the demons! Yaaaah!!

Utsusemi. To be caught by such a basic ninjutsu. Nakatarou
was a master of ninjutsu, but it seems his talent did not
pass on to you, his daughter... What a shame.
Heh. With this, the cunning mouse is barely breathing.
...I don't recall asking you to come here, Gyouon.

My apologies, Kotaro-dono. However, my I Ching divination
indicated that if I do not kill these three now, it will
lead to trouble later on, so I brought Senbi with me.
--Grrrrrrr! I can't stand still, it's not in my nature!

A wolf demon... you say? Damn! Karin, are you still
breathing? Hang in there!

This is bad! The cut is deep into the artery! If this
continues, she'll lose too much blood...!

Reinforcements of demons!? Damn! There's no way to escape
now...!

Hahaha. Even if you try to retreat, you cannot escape. Ho-
Chiku-dono lured you into the coastal cave so that no matter
how the battle turned out, you wouldn't be able to flee--
trapped in a spider's web to be finished off... A strategy
befitting an elder.

Ho-Chiku's death will not be in vain. I will send you all to
the afterlife as well.

My dear daughter, Momiji--I had considered the possibility
of you returning to our side, but seeing those defiant eyes
of yours, it seems it was a vain hope.

I have parted ways with the path of demons. I will never
return to living like a demon again!

Oh my, Momiji-san has grown quite a bit mentally, hasn't
she? If that's the case, it can't be helped. Senbi. Tear
these three apart right here. Shred them into pieces until
they're nothing but chunks of flesh. Afterwards, you may eat
them as food if you wish.

...I prefer to eat them alive rather than killing them
first. Is that alright with you?

Heh--do as you like... You may perform a dance of death if
you wish. Everyone has their own preferences when it comes
to eating

Grrrrrrrrr--!! I'll devour all three of you and absorb you
into my belly--!! Gwaaaaah!!
I know! We'll protect Karin together!

(It's no use... there are too many enemies... is this where
it ends...)

Hmph! I cannot simply stand by and watch my disciples be
killed. Stand back, mongrel.

Grrr! You--!? I thought I had killed you, yet you're still
alive!?
Masaki-sama of the Sky Fox is invincible! Nyahaha!

I've kept you waiting, Momiji-- I've come to help now that
my spiritual power has recovered to 80%. Indeed, we have
quite the formidable enemies here.

I've heard from Senbi. So you are the king of spirits that
has existed in this land since ancient times--the Spirit
Fox, are you not?

Indeed. Now I am Masaki of the Sky Fox. Are you the ninja
called Kotaro Fuma? You have a rather gloomy face, but your
presence--indeed, it seems you are quite the formidable one.
Nuuuu!? You fox brat! I'll torment and kill you!

What's this? The fake demons are quite spirited. Thinking
you've become strong just because you've banded together is
a big mistake. Take this and die--

--The forces of the Demon Grudge Party fell to the ground,
charred black!

In an instant, so many demons were--!? What an incredible
thunder strike...!

Nyahahaha! Delightful, delightful! How about that, Momiji?
My spiritual power has recovered this much!

Master, you really did come all the way to Atami. Please
make sure to tell me properly next time... I was worried
when you suddenly disappeared.

My apologies. Well, as you can see, the hot springs have
fully healed me. If my spiritual power had completely
recovered, I could have taken down those demons with a
single strike.

Dear me... My outfit has been scorched. It was my
favorite...

--! To think it could stand up after such a thunder
strike...!

Hmph! Among all these demons, there's only one real demon?
Don't overdo it when you're still recovering from injuries.
I'll let this thunder strike serve as a greeting and make my
retreat. Farewell--

You won't escape! This time I'll make sure to end your
life!!

Hmph! That's my line, you oversized mongrel! Next time we
meet, I'll cut off your tail and stuff it in your mouth!
--Masaki disappeared with Karin and the other two girls!
Grrr! Damn Masaki! Such an annoying trick--!

It can't be helped. The remaining war demons here are three
of us, plus Nyuudo who we didn't bring along, making four in
total. We're now even in number with them. It should be a
bit more enjoyable.
The demons of Fuma... it's finally just me left...

The ritual to create a world of demons is nearly complete.
Please continue to lend us your strength for the sake of
avenging Lord Ho-Chiku and the others. Lord Kotaro of the
Fuma demons--

...I will make a grave for Ho-Chiku. The rest of you return
to the temple for the ritual.

Yes. The souls of the Demon Grudge Party who died here will
also serve as fine material for the ritual as offerings.
Then, I shall take my leave first.
Grrrrr! I will definitely kill that female fox!

...Hou-Chiku. You've suffered much as my right-hand man. The
future of Fuma will be carried on by me. Rest in peace... I
shall join you before long--

Yes. If it weren't for Momiji-san's treatment, I would have
bled to death. Thank you always for healing my wounds.

You're a tough one, aren't you? Senbi's strength is
extraordinary. It was a claw strike that could have easily
bisected a normal human, right?

I am called Yugiri, the leader of the Iga ninja group--I
thank you for helping us three. Who exactly are you... or
rather, are you truly a kitsune?

It seems I have yet to introduce myself. My name is Masaki.
I have a past of being saved by Karin. I came to return the
favor.

Actually, I met her at the bathhouse the other night, and it
was fortunate to arrive at just the right moment of crisis
My sudden intrusion was cool, wasn't it?

Yes. You came at the perfect time and really saved me. Thank
you, Masaki-chan.

No need for thanks. Doing good deeds for people is my
current duty! Nyahaha
What will you do now? Will you stay in Atami?

Let's return to Edo once. We've managed to wipe out all the
demons in the coastal cave except for the war demons... Now
that the threat of demons is gone, I think Atami will be
peaceful again.

That's right. Then let's part ways here. We will return to
Edo ahead of you, Momiji. Help out at the shop in Ueno
starting tomorrow.

Eh...! Were you really serious about running a sweet tea
shop?

Indeed. If you are a disciple, then it's your duty to help
with your master's work, right? Farewell then, Karin and
Yugiri or whatever your name is--let's meet again

That kitsune named Masaki--she has quite an impatient
personality... She went back to Edo with Momiji-dono
already?

That's right. But she's not a bad yokai. She came to repay
her debt by helping me... If we could fight together, she
would be an invaluable ally.

Hmm. The lightning technique that annihilated the Demon
Grudge Party in an instant was splendid. If we meet again, I
would like to invite her to join our Iga ninja.

We'll rest at the hot spring inn before returning to Edo.
But this was another fierce battle... Ouch... It wouldn't be
wrong to take a therapeutic bath before going back.

The lie about going to Atami for a hot spring cure that we
told Oei-dono before has become true... Can you walk, Karin?

Yes, it's a bit painful, but I'm fine with this much. Let's
go into the hot springs together, Yugiri-chan, and soothe
our fatigue.

Ah. I'll join you, Karin--I'm glad we survived this time
too. The battle with the remaining war demons is near. Let's
be sure to win again.

--Karin leaned on Yugiri's shoulder as they headed towards
the hot spring inn.

Then let me speak frankly. Your father, Chutarou--he died 5
years ago.

(I can't believe what Kotaro said... Dad has to be alive...
he must be...)

When the mechanism was activated, all the doors in the
coastal cave opened!

--Health and skill power have been \c[24]fully
restored\c[0]!

Advice: For the three rocks lined up, push the middle rock
from the side last.
Gobaaah! You shall not pass any further!!
Uwaaaah!? A bunch of demons have gathered!?
It seems we can't move forward unless we defeat these guys?
Let's defeat all the demons here--
